<section id="about" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lAbout">About Tripura</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="aboutTitle">Land of <em>Maharajas & Mystique</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="aboutBody">Tripura, the "Land of Maharajas," is a northeastern state steeped in regal heritage, spiritual significance and cultural diversity. Nestled between Assam and Bangladesh, Tripura boasts a unique blend of Hindu, Buddhist and tribal traditions. Known for its magnificent palaces, ancient temples, serene lakes and vibrant tribal communities, Tripura represents Northeast India's grandeur and warmth. From the impressive Ujjayanta Palace in Agartala to sacred Kamakshi Temple, from lush natural reserves to bustling cultural centers, Tripura offers immersive experiences. The state's rich historical past as an independent kingdom, colorful handicraft traditions, diverse festivals and authentic cuisine make it a captivating destination. Tripura's commitment to preserving its heritage while embracing modernity creates a unique travel experience where ancient palaces stand alongside contemporary development.</p>
</section>

